-- Greece Gets Vote on Austerity Implementation
-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 2012-02-28T21:47:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/greece-secures-vote-on-austerity-implementation.html
Greek Prime Minister  Lucas Papademos 
secured approval of a bill on implementing austerity measures to
secure a second bailout package from the European Union and
 International Monetary Fund  in  Athens  today.  A total of 202 lawmakers voted in favor and 80 against,
Acting Parliament Speaker Grigoris Niotis said in remarks
carried live on state-run Vouli TV.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  